      • [ - ] SteveHyland - member since 03-Nov-12

        @Drifter- I've found that all statistics-based sites rate solid but unspectacular defenders low. This is largely because the things they do well aren't quantifiable- positioning, anticipation, organising those around them..... most of the things which 15 years ago made a top central defender along with the countable aspects such as tackling, clearing the ball from danger etc. Adams, Nesta, Blanc, Kohler, these players would likely rate low 7s most games according to modern-day criteria, but actually if you asked strikers of any era whether they'd rather face those 4 or typical modern-day CBs like Ramos, Thiago Silva, Boateng or Otamendi then they'd pick the latter foursome all day long.
